The paper deals with the problem of finding straight-line outerplanar drawings of outerplanar graphs with a small number of distinct edge slopes. This problem is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from combinatorics (cs.DM) and graph theory algorithms (cs.GT). Finally, the paper's results have potential applications in information visualization (cs.SI).
